{[%evp 0,8,17,17,47,70,56,32,32,31,31]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 {Against 2...
e6 we go for the Open Sicilian. Compared to 2...d6 3.d4 the variations are
less concrete. I have chosen clever lines that can be played without too much
knowledge of theory.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 {Now Black has five variations available.}
Nc6 {Taimanov Variation - see PART 1.} (4... a6 {Kan Variation - see PART 2.})
(4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 {Sicilian Four Knights - see PART 4.} (5... Bb4 {Pin
Variation - see PART 3.}) (5... d6 {Scheveningen Variation - see PART 5.})) *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "2024.01.05"]
[Round "?"]
[White "PART 1: TAIMANOV VARIATION"]
[Black "THEORETICAL OVERVIEW"]
[Result "*"]
