1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nb5 d6 6. c4 a6 7. N5c3 Nf6 8. Be2
Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Bf4 b6 11. Re1 Bb7 12. Nd2 Rc8 13. Rc1 Nd4 14. Bd3 (14. Bf1
$1 $14 {is probably more precise.}) 14... e5 $2 {This is almost always a
mistake. Over the next move White slowly improves his position.} 15. Be3 $16
Ne6 16. Bf1 g6 17. b4 Ng7 18. f3 Nd7 19. Bf2 h6 20. Rc2 {Now if Black doesn't
"do anything" White can prepare a4-a5 or just play Nd5 at some point as it
happened in the game.} Rc7 21. Nd5 $1 {Now this is very strong and gives White
a decisive positional advantage.} Bxd5 22. cxd5 $18 Ra7 23. Rc6 a5 24. bxa5
Rxa5 25. a4 Nc5 26. Nc4 Ra7 27. Nxb6 Rc7 28. a5 Qb8 29. Rxc5 Rxc5 30. Nd7 Qc7
31. Nxc5 dxc5 32. Qa4 Ra8 33. a6 Ne8 34. Rb1 Nd6 35. Qc6 Rc8 36. Qxc5 1-0

