1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nb5 d6 6. c4 Nf6 7. N5c3 Be7 8.
Be2 O-O 9. O-O b6 10. Bf4 Bb7 11. Re1 Ne5 12. Nd2 a6 13. Rc1 Qc7 {What is the
best move now? That cannot be answered, but the move played in the game and
all the alternatives mentioned are good.} 14. Bg3 (14. Bf1) (14. a3) (14. Be3)
14... g5 $5 {This is interesting, but White may profit from Black's aggression
as it also weakens his position.} 15. b4 Nfd7 16. Bf1 (16. Nf3 $1 {was quite
good.}) 16... Rac8 {Stabilizing the position is always useful.} 17. a3 Ng6 18.
Na4 Nde5 19. Nb3 {With his last two moves White is preparing c4-c5.} g4 20. Qd4
Bg5 21. Rc3 Bf6 22. Qe3 Nd7 23. Rcc1 (23. c5 $1 {would be have been quite good
- White can give the exchange as Black will badly miss his dark-squared bishop.
}) 23... e5 24. f3 {Needlessly giving Black counterplay.} ({The simple} 24. Nc3
$16 {was good enough for a clear advantage.}) 24... gxf3 25. gxf3 $2 {Black is
even better now, though White won after a complicated fight.} (25. Qxf3 $14)
25... Kh8 26. Nc3 Qd8 27. Rcd1 Bg5 28. Qd3 Be7 29. Bh3 Nf4 30. Bxf4 exf4 31.
Bxd7 Qxd7 32. Qd4+ f6 33. Kh1 Qh3 34. Nd2 Rg8 35. Rg1 Rg3 36. Qf2 Rcg8 37. Ne2
Rxg1+ 38. Rxg1 b5 39. cxb5 axb5 40. Rxg8+ Kxg8 41. Nxf4 Qh6 42. Qg3+ Kf7 43.
Qg4 Bc8 44. Qxc8 Qxf4 45. Qc3 Bd8 46. Nf1 Bb6 47. Ng3 Qe5 48. Qc6 Qd4 49. Qd7+
Kf8 50. Kg2 h5 51. Kh3 Qf2 1-0

