1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nb5 d6 6. c4 Nf6 7. N5c3 Be7 8.
Be2 b6 9. O-O Bb7 10. Bf4 O-O 11. Re1 a6 12. Bf1 Rc8 13. Nd2 Qc7 14. Rc1 Qb8 (
14... Rfe8 $2 15. Nd5 exd5 16. cxd5 $14) 15. a3 Rfd8 16. b4 Ne5 17. Bg3 ({
Another idea:} 17. h3 $5 h6 18. Qe2 Ba8 19. Qe3 $1 Ng6 20. Bh2 Nd7 21. f4)
17... Ng6 18. f4 Nd7 19. Nf3 Bf6 20. f5 {White starts some concrete action. It
was also possible and maybe objectively better to first keep improving with
for example Qd2 or Qd3.} Nge5 21. fxe6 fxe6 {A complicated position has arisen
where White's chances are maybe slightly better. He won after a complicated
fight.} 22. Qb3 Re8 23. Nb1 Bc6 24. Nbd2 Kh8 25. Kh1 Nf7 26. c5 bxc5 27. Bxa6
Rcd8 28. Bc4 Nf8 29. b5 Bb7 30. a4 Qa8 31. Bd3 Nd7 32. Bc2 Nfe5 33. Nxe5 Bxe5
34. Nc4 Bxg3 35. Qxg3 d5 36. Nd6 Rf8 37. e5 d4 38. Qh4 h6 39. Qg3 c4 40. Nxc4
Nc5 41. Nd6 d3 42. Bxd3 Nxd3 43. Qxd3 Bxg2+ 44. Kg1 Bd5 45. Qd4 Rxd6 46. exd6
Qd8 47. Rc3 Qxd6 48. Rg3 Rf6 49. Rc1 Qf8 50. a5 Rf4 51. Qe3 Bc4 52. Rxc4 Rxc4
53. b6 Ra4 54. Qe5 Rb4 55. h3 Kh7 56. Rg2 g5 57. Qc7+ Kg6 58. Qc2+ Kh5 59. Qe2+
Kg6 60. Qxe6+ Kh5 61. Qe2+ Kg6 62. Qc2+ Kh5 63. Rf2 Qd6 64. Qc3 Kh4 65. Rd2 Qf4
66. Kg2 Qe4+ 67. Qf3 Qxf3+ 68. Kxf3 Kxh3 69. Rd6 g4+ 70. Ke2 h5 71. a6 g3 72.
a7 g2 73. Rd1 1-0

