1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Bd3 Nf6 6. O-O d6 7. c4 Be7 8. Nc3
O-O 9. b3 Nbd7 (9... Nc6 10. Nxc6 {White could also retreat the knight.} bxc6
11. Bb2 $14) 10. Bb2 Re8 11. Kh1 Qc7 12. f4 {Although this position is
playable for Black it is very passive and he should avoid it in my view.} b6
13. Qe2 Bb7 14. Rae1 Rad8 {Now White went for} 15. f5 $5 {giving away the
e5-square but weakening Black's position.} Bf8 16. fxe6 fxe6 17. Bc2 Ne5 $14 {
Black has a strong knight on e5, but the d4-knight is also quite strong. White
won in the tough battle ahead.} 18. Qe3 Rb8 19. Qg3 {It was possible to target
the e6-pawn with Qh3, Nce2-f4.} Kh8 20. Nce2 Bc8 21. Nf4 b5 22. Nf3 Nfg4 23.
Ng5 Qe7 24. Qh4 h6 25. Qh5 Bd7 26. Ng6+ Nxg6 27. Nf7+ Kg8 28. Qxg4 Ne5 29. Bxe5
dxe5 30. Nxh6+ Kh8 31. Nf7+ Kg8 32. Qh5 1-0

