1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d6 {The famous Schevenigen
Variation! Nowadays it is considered a somewhat risky opening for Black, but
it is certainly playable!} 6. Be3 (6. g4 $1 {The Keres Attack is the most
dangerous system for Black, but one which requires some knowledge!}) 6... Nc6 (
6... a6 7. a4 Nc6 8. Be2 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. f4 Bd7 11. Kh1 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 Bc6
13. Bd3 Rc8 14. Qe1) 7. Qe2 $1 (7. f4 $5) 7... Be7 8. O-O-O $36 {with very
similar play to the 5...Nc6 6.a3! d6 7.Qe2!! variation! Here, I can always
play a3 and transpose, but most likely will find even more useful moves!!!} Qc7
(8... O-O 9. g4 $16) 9. g4 $1 h6 10. f4 $16 *

