1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 {a very interesting line for
White! The idea is to avoid the theory and play a Maroczy bind with c4.} Nc6 $1
{Without exaggeration, this is maybe the ONLY good move after 5.Bd3!} (5...
Nbd7 $6 {Now, we don't really need to know any theory - just play c4, as
planned, and develop the pieces to the center...with a very nice plus for
White! See PART 3.}) (5... g6 {The Dragon setup is maybe Black's second-best
choice. See PART 2.}) (5... a6 $6 {Playable for sure, but we get exactly what
we want without any pressure! See PART 3.}) (5... e5 $2 {SUPER SOS !!  THIS
MOVE IS A MISTAKE AND AFTER 6.Nf3!! white is much better! HOWEVER, MANY
PLAYERS WITH THE BLACK PIECES WILL PLAY LIKE THIS...SO BE PREPARED !!! AND GET
A HUGE ADVANTAGE! See PART 3.} 6. Nf3 $1 $16 {we will get a strong grip in the
center after playing c4! very soon !}) (5... e6 6. c4 $14 {and again this is
very similar to the lines with ...a6 and ...e6. See PART 3.}) 6. Nxc6 $1 {
This is THE SIMPLEST and a very interesting concept!! We just take on c6 and
IF BLACK PLAYS ...e6 WE PLAY c4. But if Black plays with g6-Bg7, then we
should probably avoid c4!} (6. Be3 $1 {This is another good move! Now ...g6
and ...Ng4 are playable!}) 6... bxc6 7. O-O {See PART 1.} *

