1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 g6 6. O-O $1 ({or} 6. c4 $1
Nc6 7. Ne2 $1) 6... Bg7 7. c4 O-O 8. Nc3 {White has reached a typical Maroczy
setup. We have good chances that Black is not familiar with it - players
starting with 2...d6 usually don't like to play such positions. Now if it was
White to move we would play prepare Be3 with Be2! or h3!} Nc6 {If Black
doesn't play this natural move, White has time to reach his optimal setup.} (
8... a6 9. Be2 $1 ({or} 9. h3 $1 Nc6 10. Be3 $14) 9... Nc6 10. Be3 Bd7 11. a4
$14) (8... Re8 $6 9. Be2 $1 Nc6 10. Be3) (8... h6 $6 9. Be2 $1 Nc6 10. Be3) 9.
Nde2 $1 {Our plan after ...Nc6 move is usually Nde2! to avoid exchanging
pieces, and then h3-Be3! We have no problem giving our Bd3 for the Nc6 as
after ...Ne5-Nxd3 White still is better.} (9. Be2 $4 Nxe4 $1 $17 {[%csl Rd4]})
9... Be6 (9... Bd7 10. h3 Rc8 11. Be3 $14) (9... Ne5 10. b3 Nxd3 11. Qxd3 a6
12. a4 $16 {For instance} Nd7 13. Be3 Nc5 14. Qc2) (9... a6 10. h3 Ne5 11. Be3
Nxd3 12. Qxd3 $14) 10. b3 $14 (10. h3) 10... Rc8 {SUPER SOS !!! OUR PLAN IN
THESE POSITIONS IS b3! (if we feel that black may put pressure on c4) BUT THEN
NOT Bb2! The plan is b3!-h3!-Be3!! We don't really mind if Black takes the Bd3
with Nb4-Nxd3, as White will be better! After this, the Ne2 will soon come
back on d4 since there is no Nc6 anymore.} 11. Bf4 $3 $16 {This is another
amazing move by the computer AND PROBABLY THE MOST SIMPLE WAY TO CONTINUE !!
We want to slowly stabilize our position and we don't mind about a Nh5 move
because the knight is always misplaced there!!} (11. h3 Qd7 12. Be3 Nh5 13. Kh2
$3 $16 {For instance} Ne5 14. f4 Nxd3 15. Qxd3 f5 16. Bd4 $16) (11. Bb2 $2 a6
12. Rc1 Nd7 13. Qd2 Nc5 14. Bb1 Qa5 15. Rfd1 b5 $1 $132) 11... Nh5 $2 (11...
Ne5 12. Rc1 (12. Bc2 $16) 12... Nxd3 13. Qxd3 a6 14. h3 (14. Rfd1 $16) 14...
Nd7 15. Be3 Ne5 16. Qd2 Nc6 (16... Bxh3 $2 17. f4 $1 $18) 17. Nd5 $16 (17. Nf4
$16)) 12. Be3 $16 Qa5 13. Rc1 f5 $2 14. exf5 $3 $16 {After ...f5 by Black, we
almost always take it !!!} Bxf5 15. Bxf5 Qxf5 16. h3 {White is almost winning.}
*

