1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 a6 6. c4 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. Nc3
O-O 9. Nde2 (9. h3 {is another good and playable move.} Nc6 10. Be3 (10. Nf3
Nd7 $5 $132 {[%cal Yg7c3]}) 10... Ng4 11. hxg4 Bxd4 12. Bxd4 Nxd4 13. f4 $14) (
9. Be2 $1 Nc6 10. Be3 $14 {White has reached the regular Maroczy system with
the extra tempo ...a6 for Black. However, this doesn't seem to help him too
much.}) 9... Nbd7 10. Rb1 Ne5 11. a4 Qc7 12. b3 {White prevents any
counterplay and stabilizes the position.} b6 13. Bg5 $14 Bb7 14. h3 Rac8 15.
Qd2 e6 (15... Nxd3 16. Qxd3 $14) 16. Rbc1 Qc5 17. Bc2 Nc6 18. Rfd1 Rfd8 19. Qf4
Qe5 20. Qxe5 Nxe5 21. Bb1 h6 22. Be3 1-0

