1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 e6 (5... Nbd7 $6 {and now ,
we dont really need to know any theory ...just play c4 , as plannd, and
develop the pieces in the center...with a very nice plus for white !} 6. c4 $1
Nc5 (6... Qb6 7. Nc2 $14 (7. Ne2 $14 Nc5 8. Nbc3 e6 9. O-O Be7 10. Bc2 $16) (7.
Nf3 $14 Nc5 8. Nc3 Nxd3+ 9. Qxd3 $16) 7... Nc5 8. Nc3 Nxd3+ 9. Qxd3) 7. Nc3
Nxd3+ 8. Qxd3 e6 9. O-O $16 (9. b3 $16 Be7 10. Bb2 a6 (10... O-O 11. O-O) 11.
O-O O-O 12. Rad1) 9... Be7 10. Rd1 a6 11. Qg3 $16) (5... e5 $2 {SUPER SOS !! 
THIS MOVE IS A MISTAKE AND AFTER 6.Nf3!! white is much better ! HOWEVER, MANY
PLAYERS WITH THE BLACK PIECES WILL PLAY LIKE THIS...SO BE PREPARED !!! AND GET
A HUGE ADVANTAGE !} 6. Nf3 $1 $16 {we will get a strong grip in the center
after playing c4! very soon !} Nc6 (6... d5 $2 7. exd5 Nxd5 (7... Qxd5 8. O-O
$16 e4 $4 9. Nc3 Qd8 10. Nxe4) (7... e4 8. Bb5+ Bd7 9. Nd4 Bc5 10. Bxd7+ Nbxd7
(10... Qxd7 11. c4 $16) 11. O-O O-O 12. c4 $16 (12. Nc3 $16)) 8. Nxe5 $16) 7.
O-O $16 {or 7.c4! +/-} (7. c4 $16) 7... Bg4 (7... Be7 8. c4 O-O 9. Nc3 Bg4 10.
Be2 $16 (10. Be3 $16 Nd4 11. Be2) 10... Bxf3 11. Bxf3 Nd4 12. Be3 Nxf3+ 13.
Qxf3) (7... h6 8. c4 Be7 9. Nc3 O-O 10. h3 $14 {see model game
Caruana-Nazaretyan.}) 8. c4 $3 Nd4 9. Be2 $1 $16 Nxe2+ 10. Qxe2 Be7 11. h3 Bh5
12. Nc3 Rc8 13. b3 O-O 14. Qd3 a6 15. Bg5 $16 (15. a4 $16)) (5... a6 {playable
for sure..but then we get exactly what we want without any pressure !} 6. c4 e6
(6... Nc6 7. Nxc6 $1 (7. Be3 $2 Ng4 $1 $15) (7. Ne2 $14) 7... bxc6 8. Nc3 $14 {
with typical play.}) (6... g6 7. Nc3 Bg7 8. Be2 $1 $14 {We get a standard
Maroczy position with a tempo down for us. But firstly the extra move ...a6
isn't such a big deal and secondly: does our opponent really play the Maroczy??
} (8. Be3 $4 Ng4) ({or} 8. h3 $1 Nc6 9. Be3 $1 $14) 8... O-O 9. Be3 Nc6 (9...
Nbd7 $2 10. Rc1 Nc5 11. f3 Bd7 12. Qd2 $16) 10. O-O {see 5...g6 - PART 2.}) 7.
Nc3 {and now ...once again , we do not really ned any theory ! ...all the
logical moves are good enough for an advantage !} Nc6 8. Nxc6 $1 $14 (8. Be3 $1
$14) 8... bxc6 9. O-O Be7 10. Be3 (10. Bf4 $5 e5 11. Be3) 10... O-O 11. Qe2 d5
(11... e5 12. h3 Be6 13. Rfd1 $16) 12. Rfd1 $16) 6. c4 $14 {and again this is
very similar to the lines with a6 and e6} Be7 (6... Nc6 7. Be3 $1 $14 (7. Nxc6
$1 $14)) 7. Nc3 O-O 8. O-O a6 9. Be3 $1 Nbd7 $2 {its better for black to
develop this knight to c6 here} 10. Rc1 Qc7 11. f4 $1 b6 (11... Nc5 12. Bb1 $16
) 12. b4 $3 $16 {the knight on d7 is very problematic..and whte is almost
winning !} Bb7 13. g4 $3 Rac8 14. g5 Ne8 15. f5 $18 (15. a3 $5 $16) *

