1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 a6 6. c4 e6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. Nc2
{Maybe the alternatives are a little better, but it's a matter of taste.} (8.
Nxc6 $14) (8. Be3 $14) 8... Be7 9. O-O b6 10. Be3 Bb7 11. Be2 Nb8 12. f3 Nbd7 {
After an unusual move order, we reached a classical Hedghog setup.} 13. Qd2 O-O
14. Rfd1 Qc7 15. Rac1 Rac8 16. Bf1 Rfe8 17. Nd4 Qb8 18. b3 Bd8 19. Kh1 {
White anticipates ...Bc7 and prepares to protect h2 by Bg1.} Bc7 20. Bg1 Kh8 (
20... d5 $1 $132) 21. b4 {Now White has a good game.} Rg8 22. b5 a5 23. Na4 Qa8
24. Be3 Nc5 25. Nxc5 dxc5 26. Ne2 Rgd8 27. Qe1 Qb8 28. Bg1 h6 29. Nc3 Bf4 30.
Rb1 Rxd1 31. Rxd1 Rd8 32. Na4 Qc7 33. Rxd8+ Qxd8 34. Nxc5 bxc5 35. Bxc5 Qd2 36.
Qxd2 Bxd2 37. Bd4 Nd7 38. c5 e5 39. Bf2 Nb8 40. Bc4 Bc3 41. Bd5 Bc8 42. c6 Bd4
43. Kg1 Kg8 44. b6 Na6 45. b7 Bxb7 46. cxb7 Kf8 47. Bxd4 exd4 48. e5 Ke7 49.
Kf2 Kd7 50. Bxf7 Kc7 51. Bd5 Nc5 52. e6 Nxe6 53. Bxe6 Kxb7 54. Bc4 Kb6 55. Bd3
Kc5 56. f4 Kb4 57. Kf3 Kc3 58. Ke4 a4 59. a3 Kb3 60. Kxd4 Kxa3 61. Bb5 Kb3 62.
Bxa4+ Kxa4 63. Ke5 Kb5 64. Kf5 Kc5 65. Kg6 Kd5 66. Kxg7 Ke4 67. g3 h5 68. Kg6
h4 69. gxh4 Kxf4 70. h5 Ke5 71. h6 Ke6 72. h7 Ke7 73. h8=Q Ke6 74. Qd4 Ke7 75.
Qd5 Ke8 76. Qb7 Kd8 77. Kf6 1-0

