1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bd3 a6 6. c4 e6 7. O-O Be7 8. Nc3
Nbd7 {Now both methods of developing the c1-bishop is possible.} 9. Be3 (9. b3
O-O 10. Bb2 {[%cal Yg1h1,Yf2f4]}) 9... Qc7 10. Rc1 b6 {If White can execute
both, f4 and b4, he gets a very good position.} 11. f3 ({or} 11. f4) (11. b4 $1
Bb7 (11... Ne5 12. Be2) 12. f4 $1 {Black's position is very problematic as the
d7-knight is short of good squares.} O-O 13. g4 $1 $16) 11... Bb7 12. Qe2 Rc8
$6 13. Nd5 $5 $16 {A very nice positional piece sacrifice.} exd5 14. cxd5 Nc5 (
14... Qb8 15. Nf5 {White has very good compensation.}) 15. b4 O-O 16. bxc5 dxc5
17. Nf5 $18 b5 18. Bf4 Qd7 19. Qf2 c4 20. Qg3 Bc5+ 21. Kh1 Ne8 22. Bb1 Kh8 23.
d6 g6 24. Ne7 Nxd6 25. Qh4 g5 26. Bxg5 1-0

