{[%evp 0,5,30,7,48,48,44,27]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 {In this lecture we are going to
cover} Nc6 ({and the so-called Hyper Accelerated Dragon} 2... g6) {In both
cases we will play} 3. Bc4 $5 {see the THEORETICAL OVERVIEW for the details.} (
{After} 3. d4 {there is no simple solution for White (like the 5.Bd3-line
after 2...d6) and we would need to know a lot of theory.}) ({The Rossolimo} 3.
Bb5 {is also a sound and good choice. It also does have quite some theory
though.}) *

