1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 {I don't suggest
this line but soon we will transpose to the 6.h3 line} g6 $2 (6... Bg4 {
The only good move here.}) (6... a6 7. h3 Qb6 8. Qb3) 7. Nf3 Bg7 (7... Bg4 8.
Nbd2 Nh5 9. Be3 {White again will have a clear advantage.}) 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. h3
b6 $6 {After this Black who is anyway worse, will have two bad Bishops.} (9...
Nh5 $1 10. Be3 $5 {It is always better to retreat to e3.} Qc7 11. O-O Nf4 12.
Bc2 $1 {It is important to keep your Bishop with you in such positions.}) 10.
O-O Bb7 11. Re1 $16 Rc8 (11... Nh5 12. Be3 $5 (12. Bh2 $5 Bh6 13. Nf1 Nf4 14.
Bb5 $3 Rc8 (14... e6 15. Bxc6 Bxc6 16. Ne5 Bb7 $2 17. Ng4 Bg5 18. h4 $18 f5 19.
hxg5 fxg4 20. Qxg4) 15. Bxc6 Bxc6 16. Ne5 $1 Nh5 17. Ne3 $16 (17. h4 $16))
12... Qd6 13. Nf1 Nf4 14. Bb5 a6 (14... Rfe8 15. Qd2 Ne6 16. h4 $16) 15. Bxc6
Bxc6 16. Bxf4 Qxf4 17. Rxe7) 12. Qe2 e6 13. a4 $5 {interesting but unnecessarry
} (13. Qe3 $1 $16 Re8 14. Bh6) (13. Bg5 $5 $16) (13. g4 $5 $16) 13... Na5 14.
Ne5 Nh5 15. Be3 Qc7 16. g4 Nf6 17. Bf4 $16 Qd8 18. Bg5 Qd6 19. Bf4 Qd8 20. Bg3
Nd7 21. f4 Nf6 22. Rf1 Ne8 23. f5 exf5 24. gxf5 Nf6 25. Bh4 Qd6 26. Rae1 Ne4
27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. f6 Bh6 29. Nxe4 Qd5 30. Qb5 Qxb5 31. axb5 Rfd8 32. Nxf7 Kxf7
33. Ng5+ Bxg5 34. Re7+ Kg8 35. Bxg5 Rf8 36. f7+ Kg7 37. Bf6+ Kh6 38. Rf4 g5 39.
Rg4 Bd5 40. Bxg5+ Kg7 41. Bh4+ Kh6 42. Rf4 Kg6 43. Rg4+ Kh6 44. Bf6 Rxf7 45.
Bg7+ Rxg7 46. Rgxg7 Be4 47. Rxa7 Bg6 48. b4 Nb3 49. Rgc7 Rf8 50. Rc6 Kg5 51.
Rxb6 Nd2 52. Re6 Nf3+ 53. Kh1 Kf4 54. Kg2 Ng5 55. Rxg6 hxg6 56. Ra2 Ke3 57. c4
Kxd4 58. c5 Ne6 59. b6 Rb8 60. Kg3 Kc4 61. Re2 Nd8 62. Re8 Nc6 63. Re6 Kb5
