{This was an unlucky blitz game by the powerful GM Postny!} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5
3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 e6 $2 {and after this passive move,
White gets a big advantage wthout any effort!} 7. Nd2 $1 Bd6 8. Bxd6 (8. Bg3 {
is also possible.} Qc7 9. Ngf3 O-O 10. O-O Bxg3 11. hxg3 e5 {key break to free
up Black's position.} 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Qxe5 {White only has a very small
edge.}) 8... Qxd6 9. Ngf3 O-O 10. O-O Bd7 $2 (10... e5 $1 {should have been
played!} 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Qxe5 13. Nf3) 11. Re1 $16 Rab8 12. Ne5 b5 $2
13. b4 $1 {Typical strategy to stop Black's minority attack.} a5 14. a3 Rfc8 $6
15. Nb3 a4 $2 16. Nc5 {Black is completely lost on both sides of the board.}
Be8 17. f4 Nd7 $2 18. Ncxd7 Bxd7 19. Bxh7+ Kf8 (19... Kxh7 20. Qh5+ Kg8 21.
Qxf7+ Kh7 22. Re3) 20. Qh5 Nxe5 21. fxe5 Qe7 22. Bg6 Ke8 23. Rf1 fxg6 24. Qh8+
1-0

