1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 e6 7. Nd2 (7. Nf3
Qb6 8. Qb3 {The best move to get a stable edge.} (8. Qc2 Bd7 {Planning Rc8 and
Nb4 ideas.}) (8. Qe2 {Would be the wrong choice. As you will see soon} Be7 9.
O-O O-O 10. Nbd2 Qxb2 {Black has some chances to fight back.}) 8... Qxb3 9.
axb3 {White has a great position.}) 7... Bd6 (7... Qb6 8. Rb1 {The standard
way to defend your queenside pawns.} Qa5 (8... Be7 9. Ngf3 O-O 10. O-O Bd7 11.
Ne5) 9. a3) 8. Bg3 a6 (8... O-O {is definetely better.} 9. Ngf3 Qc7 10. Qe2 {
controlling e5 square is the key!}) 9. Ngf3 O-O 10. Ne5 Qc7 11. Qe2 b5 12. Ndf3
(12. a3 {is also possible.}) (12. O-O {Intending f4-Bh4 ideas is also possible.
} b4 13. Rac1) 12... Na5 13. Rc1 Nc4 14. Bb1 Bb7 15. Qc2 g6 16. Qe2 Nd7 17. O-O
Ndxe5 18. dxe5 Be7 19. h4 h5 20. Bf4 Bf6 21. Rfe1 Rfd8 22. g3 Bg7 23. Bg5 Rdc8
24. Rcd1 Qc6 25. Nd4 Qc7 26. Bf4 Qe7 27. Kh2 Re8 28. Bg5 Qc7 29. f4 Nb6 30. g4
Qc4 31. Bd3 Qc7 32. gxh5 gxh5 33. Qxh5 Kf8 34. Bh6 Bxh6 35. Qxh6+ Ke7 36. Qf6+
Kd7 37. Qxf7+ Re7 38. Qf6 Rg8 39. Nxe6 1-0

