1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Bf4 Bd6 5. Qd2 Bf5 6. Nc3 c6 {Whenever you
see this kind of slow play with moves like c6, it is advisable to castle long
and start attacking.} 7. O-O-O $14 Ne7 8. f3 {Typical attacking strategy. In a
practical game, this will be a nightmare to play such positions as Black.} Qc7
9. Bxd6 (9. Nge2 {is fine as well.} Bxf4 10. Qxf4 Qxf4+ 11. Nxf4 {White still
has a slight edge. Remember to think before you decide to trade the queens.
It's a critical position that will shape the rest of the game.}) 9... Qxd6 10.
g4 (10. Re1 {is also possible.} O-O 11. g4 Be6 12. h4 $16 {Planning h5-h6 next.
}) 10... Be6 11. Bd3 h5 12. Qg5 hxg4 13. fxg4 $14 Nd7 14. h3 f6 15. Qe3 Bxg4
16. Re1 Kf7 17. Nge2 Bf5 18. Nf4 Bxd3 19. Nxd3 Ng6 20. Reg1 Rh4 21. Rg3 Re8 22.
Qf2 Ndf8 23. Rhg1 Rh6 24. Ne5+ Rxe5 25. dxe5 Qxe5 26. Qxa7 Qc7 27. a4 Ne6 28.
a5 Ngf4 29. a6 Rh8 30. Kb1 g5 31. axb7 Rb8 32. Nb5 cxb5 33. h4 Ne2 34. Rf3 Nxg1
35. Qxg1 gxh4 36. Qf2 Qe5 37. Re3 Qh5 38. Rf3 Rxb7 39. Rxf6+ Ke7 40. Rf5 Qd1+
41. Ka2 Kd6 42. Qh2+ Kc5 43. Qf2+ Nd4 0-1

