{A good example of the endgame with doubled d pawns!} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5
exd5 4. Bf4 Bd6 5. Qd2 Nf6 6. Nc3 Be6 7. O-O-O Nc6 8. Kb1 Bxf4 9. Qxf4 Qd6 $2 {
The endgame is very bad for Black!} 10. Qxd6 cxd6 11. f3 {stopping all
annoying threats like Ne4, Ng4.} Kd7 12. Nge2 (12. h4 $3 {Is a good idea as
well.} h5 13. Nge2 Ne7 14. Nf4 {We certainly don't wish to trade Black's LSB
in such positions. I would recommend to rather trade your light squared bishop
with Black's Knight.}) 12... g5 13. a3 a6 14. Ng3 Ne7 15. Bd3 h5 16. Nf1 g4 17.
Ne3 Rag8 18. h4 gxh3 19. gxh3 Rg3 20. h4 Rxf3 21. Rde1 Rg8 22. Kc1 Rgg3 23. Nf1
Rh3 24. Nd2 Rxh1 25. Rxh1 Rh3 26. Rxh3 Bxh3 27. Nf3 Ng6 28. Bxg6 fxg6 29. Kd2
Bf5 30. Ng5 Kc6 31. Ne2 Ne4+ 32. Nxe4 dxe4 33. Ke3 b5 34. Nf4 a5 35. Ne2 Kd5
36. b3 Ke6 37. c4 bxc4 38. bxc4 Kf6 39. Kf4 Ke6 40. Ng3 d5 41. c5 Kd7 42. Nf1
Kc6 43. Ne3 Be6 44. Ke5 Bg8 45. Kf6 Kb5 46. Kxg6 Ka4 47. Kf6 Kb5 48. Ke5 Kc6
49. a4 Bf7 50. Kf6 Bg8 51. Ke7 Bh7 52. Kf7 Kd7 53. Kg7 Ke6 54. Kxh7 1-0

