{A simple and great game demonstrating the typical plans in exchange French.} 
1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Bf4 Bd6 5. Qd2 Nf6 6. f3 $2 (6. Nc3 {is
better.}) 6... O-O (6... Qe7+ $1 {The key move, Black is completely better
according to the computer.} 7. Ne2 Bxf4 8. Qxf4 Qb4+ 9. Nbc3 Qxb2 10. Rb1 Qxc2
$17) 7. Nc3 Re8+ 8. Nge2 Nh5 $2 9. Bxd6 $16 (9. Bg5 {troubling Black a bit
first.} Be7 10. Bxe7 Rxe7 11. O-O-O $16 {White will plan g4-h4-g5-h5.}) 9...
Qxd6 10. O-O-O $16 c6 11. g4 Nf6 12. Ng3 $1 {planning Bd3-Nf5.} (12. Qf4 $1 {
is a good choice for those who prefer endgames.} Qxf4+ 13. Nxf4 Nbd7 14. h4 Nf8
15. Bd3 {White has a huge space advantage.}) 12... Qe6 13. g5 (13. Bd3 {
would be a better choice. Usually you would like to get all your pieces before
the final blow.} Qe3 14. Rde1 Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Rd8 16. h4 Na6 17. Bxa6 bxa6 18.
Na4) 13... Nfd7 14. Bd3 Qe3 15. Qxe3 Rxe3 16. Nf5 Re8 17. Rde1 Rf8 18. h4 Nb6
19. Ne7+ Kh8 20. h5 Na6 21. g6 Nb4 22. gxf7 Nxd3+ 23. cxd3 Bd7 24. Ng6+ 1-0

