1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 $5 {this is another good and simple line
for White. We have many ways to play such a position..we will try to avoid
theory as much as possible of course!} (4. Bf4) 4... Nc6 5. Bf4 Bd6 6. Bxd6
Qxd6 7. c3 Nge7 8. Bd3 $1 {the bishop is btter placed on d3!} Bf5 9. O-O O-O
10. Re1 Rfe8 11. Na3 $14 {this simplified position is in fact very unpleasant
for Black ! The Knight stands very badly on c6 , making d5 and b7 potential
weaknesses aganst sudden attacks!} a6 12. Nc2 Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Ng6 14. g3 Nce7 15.
h4 $16 (15. Re2 $16 {again Black has a problem with both of his knights while
White has simple and logical play!}) 15... Nf8 16. Re2 Qg6 17. Qxg6 Nexg6 18.
Rae1 Rxe2 19. Rxe2 Ne6 20. Nb4 Ne7 (20... c6 21. Nd3 (21. h5 Ne7 22. Ne5)) 21.
Ng5 a5 22. Nd3 Nxg5 23. Rxe7 Ne6 24. Ne5 a4 25. Nxf7 a3 26. b3 Ra6 27. Ne5 Kf8
28. Rd7 c5 29. Rxd5 cxd4 30. cxd4 Ra8 31. Nd7+ Ke7 32. Nc5 Ra5 33. Re5 1-0

