1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Bf5 5. Bd3 $1 {Trading the Bishops to
get a head start in developement.} Bxd3 6. Qxd3 Nc6 (6... c6 7. Qe2+ $3 {
Amazing trickery to force Black to play Qe7.} Qe7 (7... Be7 8. O-O Nf6 9. Re1
$16 {When Black has some troubles in completing his developement.}) 8. Be3 $1
$14 {Where Black has troubles to get his pieces out.}) 7. O-O Qd7 8. Re1+ Nge7
9. Bd2 $3 {Black can hardly move now! White is planning b4-b5.} f6 (9... O-O-O
10. b4 $16 Nf5 11. b5 Nce7 12. a4 {with huge kingside attack.}) 10. b4 a6 11.
a4 g5 12. Na3 g4 13. Nh4 Kf7 14. b5 axb5 15. Nxb5 Ng6 16. Qf5 Rd8 17. Qh5 Nce7
18. Bf4 Kg7 19. Bxc7 Rc8 20. Rxe7+ Bxe7 21. Nf5+ Kf7 22. Bd6 Bf8 23. Bxf8 Kxf8
24. Re1 1-0

