1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Bg4 5. h3 Bh5 6. Qe2+ {A very powerful
idea} Qe7 7. Qxe7+ {is a big mistake.} (7. Be3 $1 {The typical move and we can
quickly castle long. We also have some free tempo's with g4-h4-h5 later.} Nc6
8. Nc3 O-O-O 9. g4 Bg6 10. O-O-O {And Black has problems in completing his
developement.}) 7... Bxe7 8. Ne5 f6 9. Nd3 Nc6 10. c3 Bd6 $2 {Very bad move,
Black should not allow dark squared bishop trades.} 11. Bf4 Kd7 12. Bxd6 Kxd6
13. Na3 a6 14. Nc5 Rb8 15. Kd2 $16 {White again has a huge advantage.} Bf7 16.
Re1 Na5 17. Nc2 ({A sample line goes like} 17. Bd3 Nc4+ 18. Bxc4 dxc4 19. Re2
$18 Ne7 20. Rhe1 Rhe8 21. Re6+ Bxe6 22. Rxe6+ Kd5 23. Nc2 a5 24. Ne3# {with a
pretty checkmate.}) 17... Nc4+ 18. Kc1 b6 19. Nxa6 Ra8 20. Nab4 c5 21. dxc5+
bxc5 22. Bxc4 dxc4 23. Rd1+ Kc7 24. Nd5+ Kc6 25. Nde3 Rxa2 26. Na3 Ra1+ 27. Kd2
Ra2 28. Nexc4 Ne7 29. Ra1 Rd8+ 30. Ke2 Bxc4+ 31. Nxc4 Rda8 32. Rxa2 Rxa2 33.
Kd3 Nd5 34. g3 Nb6 35. Nxb6 Kxb6 36. Kc2 c4 37. Re1 Ra7 38. h4 Kc5 39. h5 g6
40. h6 Kd5 41. Re8 f5 42. Rg8 Re7 43. Kd2 Rb7 44. Rg7 Rxb2+ 45. Ke1 Rb1+ 46.
Ke2 Rb2+ 47. Kf3 Rc2 48. Rxh7 Rxc3+ 49. Kg2 Ra3 50. Rg7 Ra8 51. h7 Rh8 52. Kf3
c3 53. Ke2 Kd4 54. Kd1 Ke4 55. Rc7 Kf3 56. Ke1 c2 57. Kf1 Rxh7 58. Rc3+ Kg4 59.
Rxc2 g5 60. Kg2 Rd7 61. f3+ Kh5 62. Kh3 g4+ 63. fxg4+ fxg4+ 64. Kg2 Rd5 65. Rc8
