1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bd3 Bd6 6. O-O ({The theory
continues with} 6. Qe2+ Qe7 7. Qxe7+ {with slightly better endgames.}) 6... O-O
7. Bg5 c6 (7... Bg4 {is critical as well.} 8. h3 Bh5 9. Nbd2 c6 10. c4 {
Important break to create imbalances.} dxc4 11. Nxc4 Bc7 12. Nce5 {The IQP
favours White as he has better activity.}) 8. c3 Bg4 9. Nbd2 Nbd7 10. Re1 Qc7
