1. d4 d6 2. e4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 Bg7 5. f3 O-O 6. Qd2 c6 7. Bh6 (7. g4 Nbd7
8. h4 h5) (7. h4 h5 (7... Nbd7 8. h5 Nxh5 9. Nge2)) 7... b5 8. h4 b4 (8... Nbd7
9. h5 $1 Bb7 (9... Nxh5 $2 10. Rxh5 $1 gxh5 11. Qg5 $18) 10. hxg6 fxg6 11. Bxg7
{We want to force Black to take with the king on g7.} (11. Nge2 {allows} Rf7)
11... Kxg7 12. Qh6+ Kg8 13. O-O-O {Black is very close to be checkmated, e.g.}
e5 14. Nh3 Rf7 15. Ng5 Rg7 16. Qxg7+ $1 $18) (8... e5 9. O-O-O $16 exd4 $140
10. Bxg7 Kxg7 (10... dxc3 11. Qh6) 11. Qxd4) 9. Nce2 Re8 10. Bxg7 Kxg7 11. h5
$1 (11. Qxb4 {White could also have taken the pawn, but it's better to
continue attacking!}) 11... e5 ({What happens after Black defends with} 11...
Rh8 12. O-O-O a5 13. h6+ $1 {We change our plan and no longer play for the
attack, but use the fact that Black has great difficulties in bringing the
h8-rook back into the game!} Kf8 14. Nf4 $18 {[%cal Yg1h3] White continues his
development. Black's counterplay on the queenside will never be effective
without the h8-rook!}) 12. hxg6 fxg6 13. O-O-O Qa5 14. Kb1 Be6 15. Nc1 $18 {
Comfortably defending against Black's only threat. White will sooner or later
start a decisive attack on the kingside.} Nbd7 16. Nge2 Nb6 17. Nb3 Qa4 (17...
Bxb3 18. Qh6+ Kg8 19. cxb3 $18) 18. g4 Nc4 19. Qh6+ Kg8 20. g5 Nh5 21. Ng3 Bf7
22. Rxh5 gxh5 23. Nf5 1-0

