Bh6, but loses too much time. White can play} 7. a4 {and go for short castling.
} ({or} 7. O-O-O {and play in the center.})) 7. Bh6 O-O $2 (7... Bxh6 $142 8.
Qxh6 Nbd7 $14) 8. h4 $16 c5 (8... e5 9. Bxg7 Kxg7 10. O-O-O exd4 11. Qxd4 Nc6
12. Qd2 h5 13. Nge2 {[%cal Ye2f4] followed by Nf4 and at some moment g2-g4.})
9. d5 e6 10. h5 b4 11. Nce2 exd5 12. hxg6 fxg6 13. Bxg7 (13. exd5 $2 Ra7 (13...
Rf7 14. Bxg7 Rxg7)) 13... Kxg7 14. Qh6+ Kg8 15. Nf4 Qe7 16. O-O-O Nc6 (16...
dxe4 17. Bc4+ Kh8 18. Nxg6#) (16... Qg7 17. Qg5) 17. Rxd5 Qg7 18. Qg5 Nxd5 19.
Bc4 Qe5 20. Bxd5+ Kg7 21. Rxh7+ $1 Kxh7 22. Qxg6+ Kh8 23. Qh6# 1-0

