1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f3 Bg7 5. Be3 a6 6. Qd2 b5 7. Bh6 $5 {Since
black has played ...Nf6, we can always play Bh6 and then: both options are
open for white after the exchange on h6 - we can go for 0-0 or 0-0-0 !!} O-O $2
(7... Bxh6 $1 8. Qxh6 Nbd7 (8... e6 9. Nh3 Qe7 10. O-O-O $5 (10. Bd3 $5 Nbd7
11. O-O c5 12. dxc5 dxc5 13. Nf2 c4 14. Be2 $14)) 9. Nh3 (9. O-O-O $5) 9... c5
10. d5 Nb6 11. Ng5 $16) 8. h4 $16 c5 9. Nge2 b4 10. Nd1 (10. Nd5 $1 {It made a
lot of sense to exchange the "defender" on f6!} Nxd5 11. exd5 $16) 10... Nc6
11. d5 Ne5 12. Bxg7 Kxg7 13. Ne3 $6 (13. Ng3 $1 h5 14. Ne3 $14) 13... h5 (13...
Nh5 $1 $15) 14. Nf4 a5 15. Nc4 Nxc4 16. Bxc4 Ba6 17. Qd3 Bxc4 18. Qxc4 a4 19.
O-O a3 20. b3 Nd7 21. Qe2 Ne5 22. Rac1 e6 23. g3 g5 24. Nxh5+ Kg6 25. f4 gxf4
26. Nxf4+ Kh7 27. dxe6 Qf6 28. Qh5+ Kg8 29. Nd5 Qxe6 30. Nf6+ 1-0

