1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. Be3 a6 {Whenever Black delays ...Nf6 and plays
on the queenside, we usually go for short castling!} 5. Qd2 b5 6. f3 Nd7 (6...
Bb7 {Now there are a few ways to develop and prepare 0-0.} 7. Nh3 $1 (7. Nge2
$5) 7... Nd7 (7... b4 8. Nd1 a5 9. a3 $1 $16 {Black cannot keep his pawn
structure on the queenside.}) 8. Be2 Ngf6 9. O-O $14) 7. Nh3 Bb7 (7... Ngf6 8.
Nf2 Bb7 ({If Black goes for short castling} 8... O-O {we can switch plans and
castle long and attack on the kingside.} 9. O-O-O $1) 9. a4 b4 10. Ncd1 c5 11.
dxc5 dxc5 12. Bh6 $14 {[%csl Ge3][%cal Yd1e3]}) 8. a4 (8. Be2 $14) 8... c6 9.
Be2 Ngf6 10. O-O O-O 11. Nf2 Rc8 12. Rfc1 $14 (12. axb5 axb5 13. Nd3 Qc7 14.
Rfd1 $14) 12... Qc7 13. Ncd1 e5 14. c4 $2 (14. dxe5 Nxe5 (14... dxe5 $2 15. c4
$1 $16) 15. Bh6 $14) 14... exd4 15. Bxd4 b4 $1 $15 16. b3 c5 17. Bb2 Rfe8 18.
Nd3 Ne5 19. N1f2 Nfd7 20. Rd1 Nxd3 21. Nxd3 Ne5 22. Nf2 Rcd8 23. Rab1 Nc6 24.
Bxg7 Kxg7 25. Ng4 Qe7 26. Qh6+ Kh8 27. Bd3 Bc8 28. Ne3 Qf8 29. Qxf8+ Rxf8 30.
Nc2 Kg7 31. Kf2 f6 32. Be2 Kf7 33. f4 Bb7 34. Bf3 Rfe8 35. Rd3 Na5 36. Re1 Re7
37. e5 Bxf3 38. Kxf3 fxe5 39. fxe5 Rxe5 40. Rxe5 dxe5 41. Rxd8 Nxb3 42. Ke4 Ke7
43. Rb8 Na5 44. Kd5 Kd7 45. Kxc5 b3 46. Na1 e4 47. Nxb3 e3 48. Nxa5 e2 49. Rb1
1-0

