{In this game, both sides played very well up to some point! Black delayed
short castling and White castled short !!} 1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. f3 g6 4. Nc3
c6 5. Be3 b5 6. Qd2 Bg7 7. Bd3 $5 (7. Bh6 $5) (7. a4 $1 b4 8. Nd1 a5 9. Bd3 $14
) 7... Nbd7 8. a4 b4 9. Nd1 a5 {Again the same harmonious arrangement of minor
pieces as in the previous game!} 10. Ne2 $14 e5 11. c3 {Defending the center,
to be able to take back with a pawn on d4.} O-O 12. O-O (12. Bh6 $2 Nxe4 $1 13.
Bxe4 Qh4+ 14. g3 Qxh6 $17) 12... d5 $5 13. Nf2 $1 ({In such situations, we
don't want to invite our opponent's pieces to the center! So we don't play
something like} 13. exd5 $2 Nxd5 {[%csl Gd5]} 14. dxe5 $2 Nxe5 $17 {[%csl Gd5,
Ge5]}) 13... bxc3 14. bxc3 Qe7 15. Bg5 $1 {[%cal Yf3f4]} Ba6 $2 16. Bxa6 Rxa6 {
Now in many variations the rook will be hanging on a6!} 17. f4 $1 $16 h6 18.
Bxf6 Nxf6 19. Qd3 Qa7 20. fxe5 dxe4 21. Nxe4 $18 Nd7 22. Kh1 c5 23. Nf4 cxd4
24. cxd4 Rd8 25. e6 fxe6 26. Nxg6 Nf8 (26... Qxd4 27. Qxa6) 27. Nxf8 Rxf8 28.
Rxf8+ Kxf8 29. Rf1+ Kg8 30. Qg3 Rc6 31. Nf6+ Kf8 32. Qg6 Rc8 33. Nh5+ 1-0

