1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. Be3 Nf6 5. f3 e5 $2 6. dxe5 $1 {This leads to
a much better endgame for White. We don't have to give checkmate in every game!
} (6. Nge2 $5 $14) 6... dxe5 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. Bc4 Be6 $2 9. Bxe6 fxe6 10. Nh3
$3 $16 {The endgame is horrible for Black - his doubled pawns are easy targets!
} Nbd7 11. a4 Ke7 12. Nf2 Ne8 13. Ke2 Nd6 14. Rhd1 a6 15. b3 Nb8 16. Nb1 Nc6
17. c3 b6 18. Na3 Nf7 19. Nc4 Bh6 20. Bxh6 Nxh6 21. b4 Nf7 22. Nd3 Kf6 23. a5
Rhb8 24. Ra2 Nd6 25. Nxd6 cxd6 26. axb6 Rxb6 27. Nb2 Na7 28. Nc4 Rc6 29. Nxd6
Ke7 30. Rad2 Rxc3 31. Nb7 Nb5 32. Rd7+ Kf6 33. Rxh7 Nd4+ 34. Kf2 Rc2+ 35. Kg3
Ra7 36. h4 Rc8 37. Rd7 Rc4 38. Nc5 Rxd7 39. Nxd7+ Kg7 40. Ra1 Ne2+ 41. Kg4 Rxb4
42. Nxe5 Rb5 43. f4 Rb3 44. Nf3 Rb4 45. Rxa6 Rxe4 46. Ra7+ Kf6 47. g3 Re3 48.
Ra5 Nc3 49. Re5 Ne4 50. Kh3 Rxf3 51. Rxe4 Ra3 52. Re5 Rb3 53. Kg4 Ra3 54. h5
gxh5+ 55. Rxh5 Rb3 56. Rh6+ Kf7 57. Kh4 Rf3 58. Kg4 Ra3 59. Rh1 Kf6 60. Rf1 Ra4
61. Kh5 Ra2 62. Rf3 Rh2+ 63. Kg4 Rb2 64. Re3 Rb1 65. Kf3 Rf1+ 66. Kg2 Ra1 67.
g4 Rb1 68. Kf3 Rf1+ 69. Ke4 Ra1 70. g5+ Kf7 71. Rd3 Re1+ 72. Re3 Ra1 73. Kf3
Rf1+ 74. Kg3 Rg1+ 75. Kf2 Ra1 76. Rh3 Ra4 77. Kg3 Re4 78. Rh7+ Kg6 79. Rh6+ Kg7
80. Kf3 Re1 81. Rf6 Kg8 82. Rg6+ Kf7 83. Rh6 Kg7 84. Rh2 Rf1+ 85. Ke4 Re1+ 86.
Kd4 Rd1+ 87. Ke3 Ra1 88. Rc2 Re1+ 89. Kf2 Ra1 90. Rc7+ Kg6 91. Re7 Kf5 92. Rf7+
