1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 c6 6. Be2 Nd7 7. Nf3 e6 $2 8.
O-O Qc7 9. Re1 $1 Be7 10. c4 N5f6 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Bd3 $1 $16 Rd8 13. Qe2 Nf8
14. Bg5 Ng6 15. g3 b6 16. h4 Bb7 17. Rad1 Re8 18. Ne5 Nxe5 19. dxe5 Nd7 20. Qe4
(20. Bxh7+ {was a very tempting continuation:} Kxh7 21. Qd3+ Kg8 22. Qxd7 {
, with a clear advantage.}) 20... Nf8 21. Qg4 Rad8 22. Bf6 Ng6 23. h5 gxf6 24.
hxg6 f5 25. gxf7+ $1 (25. gxh7+ Kh8 26. Qh5 {was less convincing.}) 25... Kxf7
26. Bxf5 $1 exf5 27. e6+ Kf6 28. Qh5 Kg7 29. Qf7+ Kh8 {[%tqu "En","White is
down a piece, but he is very active. How can White finish the game
victoriously?","Exploit the power of your passed pawn and the tension on the
d-file.","Use your d1-rook for the decisive blow!","d1d7","This neat move
decides the game.",4]} 30. Rd7 $1 {[%csl Gd7,Ge6,Re7,Re8,Gf7] After this
powerful blow, Black's position falls apart.} Qc8 (30... Rxd7 {loses to} 31.
Qxe8+ Kg7 32. exd7) 31. Rxe7 (31. Kg2 Rxd7 $140 32. Rh1 c5+ 33. Nd5 Bh4 34.
exd7 {was another winning continuation.}) 31... Rxe7 32. Qxe7 c5 33. Qf6+ Kg8
34. Nd5 (34. Qf7+ Kh8 35. e7 Re8 36. Re6 {/\Rh6 was an appealing alternative.})
34... Bxd5 35. Qf7+ Kh8 36. cxd5 Rf8 37. Qxf8+ Qxf8 38. e7 Qe8 39. d6 {, and
Black resigned, as the threat 40.d7 cannot be parried.} 1-0

